How Worried Should We Be About Screen Time During the Pandemic?

The coronavirus pandemic ended the screen time debate: Screens won. We all now find ourselves on our screens for school, for work and for connecting with family and friends during this time of social distancing and increased isolation.

But should we be worried about this excessive screen use right now? Or should we finally get over it and embrace the benefits of our digital devices?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Screen time comes with a price tag.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: When the world of screens becomes our predominant reality, we can become increasingly detached from ‘reality’ and exist more and more in the limbo of

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Gamers spend hours and hours every day, every week, every month and every year playing virtual reality games.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A gamer may have difficulties reading social cues, they may have difficulties organizing their lives, they may have difficulties functioning in the world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I do not believe that there is a right canned amount of how much screen time someone should use.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Those signs include anything from distracting yourself with work, to constantly being on your phone while interacting with people in ‘real’ life.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Being wary of screen time is not out of line with appreciating the benefits that our devices provide.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If it does, then I believe that you are overindulging in your screen time.
